enumerations.name: CanAddressingModeType
enumerations.note: Indicates whether standard or extended CAN identifiers are used Aggregated by CanFrameTriggering.canAddressingMode, IEEE1722TpAcfCanPart.canAddressingMode

enumerations.name: CanFrameRxBehaviorEnum
enumerations.note: Defines different CAN protocols for frame reception behavior. Aggregated by CanFrameTriggering.canFrameRxBehavior

literals.name: any
literals.description:
This CAN frame may be received as both, CAN 2.0 and CAN FD.
Tags: atp.EnumerationLiteralIndex=0

literals.name: can20
literals.description:
This CAN frame shall be received as CAN 2.0 only. In case the CAN frame is received as CAN FD it is discarded during reception.
Tags: atp.EnumerationLiteralIndex=1

literals.name: canFd
literals.description:
This CAN frame shall be received as CAN FD only. In case the CAN frame is received as CAN 2.0 it is discarded during reception.
Tags: atp.EnumerationLiteralIndex=2

enumerations.name: CanFrameTxBehaviorEnum
enumerations.note: Defines different CAN protocols for frame transmission behavior. Aggregated by CanFrameTriggering.canFrameTxBehavior, IEEE1722TpAcfCanPart.canFrameTxBehavior

literals.name: can20
literals.description:
This CAN frame shall be sent as CAN 2.0 only.
Tags: atp.EnumerationLiteralIndex=0

literals.name: canFd
literals.description:
This CAN frame shall be sent as CAN FD.
Tags: atp.EnumerationLiteralIndex=1
